ization in general - is a fairly black box. I already have SCM2 - and sadly neglected to do enough tests before getting it - but I would like to share my results with SCM2 and hope the wizard community want to help with data too.<br>
<br>
I did a test today with SCM2.<br>
Setup:<br>
255 wisdom<br>
+980 mana<br>
23 mana/tick standing (Innate =1, MC2=2, BAofR=6 and C3=14)<br>
<br>
I then started casting from FM till I couldnt cast a 50 mana spell - repeating this trial 10 times.<br>
<br>
5 times I got:<br>
- 4 GCH, 1 CH, 1 Remedy (4975mana)<br>
4 times I got:<br>
- 4 GCH, 1 CH, 1 Remedy, 1 Abolish Poison (5075mana)<br>
1 time I got:<br>
- 4 GCH, 1 CH, 1 Remedy, 1 Abolist Poison, 1 Cure Disease (5125mana)<br>
<br>
So, on average I was able to cast 5030 mana worth of spell over a period of approx 90 sec.<br>
<br>
Maybe others could perform similar tests - someone without SCM, as well as someone with SCM1 and SCM3 would be great. <br>
<br>
I will also try to perform a similar test using another spell type than my main spec and post my results. Hint - getting a mage with mod rod 2 to help speeds this up - alot. Too bad mine had to camp before I got far :/<br>
<br>
That way we can fairly easily get an idea just how much SCM does - or doesnt - help.<br>
<br>
