Specialization is a random roll that gives you the possibility of a 50% mana reduction in the cost of the spell. <br>
<br>
A specialization of 200 gives you a 20% chance of reducing a spells mana cost by 50% (thus a 10% overall gain on average)<br>
<br>
A specialization of 50 gives you a 5% chance of reducing a spells mana cost by 50% (thus a 2.5% overall gain on average)<br>
<br>
--Spell Casting Mastery 1 increases this chance by 5% so you have an additional 5% chance of reducing a spells mana cost by 50% (thus an additional 2.5% overall gain on average)<br>
<br>
--Spell Casting Mastery 2 increases this chance by 15% so you have an additional 15% chance of reducing a spells mana cost by 50% (thus an additional 7.5% overall gain on average)<br>
<br>
--Spell Casting Mastery 3 increases this chance by 30% so you have an additional 30% chance of reducing a spells mana cost by 50% (thus an additional 15% overall gain on average)<br>
<br>
<br>
Thus a person with Spell Casting Mastery 2 casting their 200 specialization would have a 20% chance (200 spec) PLUS a 15% chance (SCM2) for a total of a 35% chance of reducing their mana by 50% on a spell. This would be an average overall gain of 17.5%.<br>
<br>
